HEADWORD: Shepherdess
<hw>Shep"herd*ess</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A woman who tends sheep;
hence, a rural lass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She put herself into the garb of a <qex>shepherdess</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shepherdia</ent>⟦br⟧
